\begin{question}
A friend asks you to recommend a book to read. You suggest a book and then ask: "Do you like reading fiction or non-fiction books?" How can you use this question to help you better recommend a book to your friend?
\end{solution}
This question helps you better recommend a book to your friend by giving you more information about their reading preferences. If your friend likes reading fiction, you can suggest a novel
